us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameQuaternionBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameQuaternionBasics, FixedFrameTuple4DBasics, FrameChangeable, FrameQuaternionReadOnly, FrameTuple4DBasics, FrameTuple4DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.orientation.interfaces.Orientation3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.orientation.interfaces.Orientation3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.QuaternionBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.QuaternionReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameQuaternion

    public interface FrameQuaternionBasics
extends FixedFrameQuaternionBasics, FrameTuple4DBasics, FrameChangeable
    Write and read interface for a quaternion expressed in a changeable reference frame, i.e. the reference frame in which this quaternion is expressed can be changed.

    In addition to representing a QuaternionBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameQuaternionBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on quaternions occur in the same coordinate system. Also, via the method FrameChangeable.changeFrame(ReferenceFrame), one can easily calculates the value of a quaternion in different reference frames.

    Because a FrameQuaternionBasics extends QuaternionBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring QuaternionBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameQuaternionBasics.

      • setIncludingFrame

        default void setIncludingFrame(ReferenceFrame referenceFrame,
                               us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DReadOnly rotationVector)
        Sets this frame quaternion to the same orientation described by the given rotation vector rotationVector and sets the frame to the given referenceFrame.

        WARNING: a rotation vector is different from a yaw-pitch-roll or Euler angles representation. A rotation vector is equivalent to the axis of an axis-angle that is multiplied by the angle of the same axis-angle.

        Parameters:
        referenceFrame - the new reference frame for this frame quaternion.
        rotationVector - vector the rotation vector used to set this quaternion. Not modified.

      • setEulerIncludingFrame

        default void setEulerIncludingFrame(ReferenceFrame referenceFrame,
                                    us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DReadOnly eulerAngles)
        Sets this quaternion to represent the same orientation as the given Euler angles eulerAngles and sets the frame to the given referenceFrame.

        This is equivalent to this.setYawPitchRollIncludingFrame(referenceFrame, eulerAngles.getZ(), eulerAngles.getY(), eulerAngles.getX()).

        Parameters:
        referenceFrame - the new reference frame for this frame quaternion.
        eulerAngles - the Euler angles to copy the orientation from. Not modified.

      • setEulerIncludingFrame

        default void setEulerIncludingFrame(ReferenceFrame referenceFrame,
                                    double rotX,
                                    double rotY,
                                    double rotZ)
        Sets this quaternion to represent the same orientation as the given Euler angles rotX, rotY, and rotZ and sets the frame to the given referenceFrame.

        This is equivalent to this.setYawPitchRollIncludingFrame(referenceFrame, rotZ, rotY, rotX).

        Parameters:
        referenceFrame - the new reference frame for this frame quaternion.
        rotX - the angle to rotate about the x-axis.
        rotY - the angle to rotate about the y-axis.
        rotZ - the angle to rotate about the z-axis.
